We will replace the `sorry` in the `map_eq` field.
We need to show that `map (fun ω ↦ X ω ∩ Y ω) P = @ProbabilityTheory.bernoulliOn ι u (p * q)`.
This means showing that for any set `S`, the probability of `X ω ∩ Y ω ∈ S` is equal to the probability of a Bernoulli distributed variable with parameter `p*q` being in `S`.

